cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the effect of different visualization designs on the perception of causality in data, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of text descriptions and natural language processing (cs.CL), as well as data aggregation and analysis (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of different visual encodings and their impact on perception (cs.SI), and the potential implications for data visualization in different contexts (cs.CY).
